latestPosts.caption:
Thesis collection : The Answer 

Shamans, often regarded as messengers from the divine, practice one of the world’s oldest spiritual traditions, with deep roots in regions like Mongolia and Northern Europe. As a half-Mongolian, I am drawn to explore the mysterious and profound history of shamanic culture and attire, seeking to uncover the wisdom and symbolism embedded in this ancient practice.

Designer: Me

latestPosts.caption:
Creative design final project - forbidden love 

The inspiration for this project was form a fictional disease called 花は気病(hanahaki syndrome) originated from a Japanese novel. The sickness is described as: “victim coughs up flower petals when they suffer from one-sided love.” 

I wanted to show the struggle and uncomfort of the sickness therefore harden the outer layer of clothing with resin, covering the soft fabric flower that is under the pannier.
Model: @riikou_

latestPosts.caption:
AAS exhibition Critics project: Chiaroscuro 

Chiaroscuro, in art, is the use of strong contrasts between light and dark. This project is heavily insired by the architect Ando Tadao, best known for his minimalist apraoch to architecure and unique persuit of light.
In the collection Chiaroscuro, it explores many different ways to express light and shadow, finding the middle ground between architectures and the human body. 

So honored to be chosen for the exhibition, this is my first time exploring a more minimalistic design, honestly I was feeling really uncertain about my choices and doubt myself throughout the process but I am really proud of how it turned out at the end ☺️
